<span class=\"fn\">g</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">↑<a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a><span class=\"fn\">x</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Group/Defs.html#Norm.norm\">‖</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Corollary of Hahn-Banach. Given an element `x` of a normed space with `‖x‖ ≠ 0`, there\nexists an element of the dual space, of norm `1`, whose value on `x` is `‖x‖`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/HahnBanach.html#exists_dual_vector","kind":"theorem","line":148,"name":"exists_dual_vector","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/HahnBanach.lean#L148-L164"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Module/HahnBanach.html#Submodule.ClosedComplemented.of_finiteDimensional\"><span class=\"name\">Submodule</span>.<span class=\"name\">ClosedComplemented</span>.<span class=\"name\">of_finiteDimensional</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Field/Basic.html#NontriviallyNormedField\">NontriviallyNormedField</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/RCLike/Basic.html#IsRCLikeNo